The State Fair Board shall be composed of fifteen (15) members, as follows:
The Governor;
The Commissioner;
The dean of the College of Agriculture of the University of Kentucky;
Nine (9) members appointed from the state at large by the Governor with due consideration to geographical distribution throughout the state;
One (1) member appointed by the Governor selected from a list provided by the Kentucky Association of Fairs and Horse Shows of six (6) eligible members of the association; and
One (1) member shall be appointed from the state at large by the President of the Senate of the Kentucky General Assembly and one (1) member shall be appointed from the state at large by the Speaker of the House of Representatives of the Kentucky General Assembly.
